**[Lucas Ward](https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lucas.l.ward)** opened **[BATCH-126](https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-126?redirect=false)** and commented

If a job has already run, and a new step is added to that same job instance (meaning with the same JobIdentifier), then the SimpleJobRepository won't load up the new step because the findStep method ignores that it's null:

    	StepInstance step = stepDao.findStep(job, stepConfiguration.getName());
    		if (step != null) {

    			step.setStepExecutionCount(stepDao.getStepExecutionCount(step.getId()));

    			steps.add(step);
    		}

I'm not sure that the repository should create a blank step in the same instance.  If the configuration has been modified to add a new step, then a new instance should be created.  However, perhaps an exception should be thrown?  Either way, just not processing that step isn't the best solution.


