When a runtime exception is thrown in `org.springframework.batch.core.JobExecutionListener#afterJob`, the error message in the log is:

```
Exception encountered in afterStep callback
```

while it should be

```
Exception encountered in afterJob callback
```

Here is an example:

```java
//create job repository
JobRepository jobRepository = new MapJobRepositoryFactoryBean().getObject();

// create job
AbstractJob job = new AbstractJob("myJob") {

	@Override
	public Step getStep(String stepName) {
		return null;
	}

	@Override
	public Collection<String> getStepNames() {
		return Collections.emptyList();
	}

	@Override
	protected void doExecute(JobExecution jobExecution) {
		System.out.println("executing job");
		jobExecution.setStatus(BatchStatus.COMPLETED);
		jobExecution.setExitStatus(ExitStatus.COMPLETED);
	}


};
job.setJobRepository(jobRepository);
job.registerJobExecutionListener(new JobExecutionListener() {
	@Override
	public void beforeJob(JobExecution jobExecution) {
		System.out.println("before job");
	}

	@Override
	public void afterJob(JobExecution jobExecution) {
		System.out.println("after job");
		throw new RuntimeException("Boom!");
	}
});
job.afterPropertiesSet();

// execute job
JobExecution jobExecution = jobRepository.createJobExecution("myJob", new JobParameters());
job.execute(jobExecution);

// prints:
// before job
// executing job
// after job
// Exception encountered in afterStep callback
```

The job has no steps (which is completely valid) and the error message is obviously incorrect.

BTW, errors [are handled for `JobExecutionListener#afterJob`](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-batch/blob/master/spring-batch-core/src/main/java/org/springframework/batch/core/job/AbstractJob.java#L358-L362) but [not for `JobExecutionListener#beforeJob`](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-batch/blob/master/spring-batch-core/src/main/java/org/springframework/batch/core/job/AbstractJob.java#L310) in `AbstractJob`. Errors in the `beforeJob` methods should also be logged for consistency.


